title: Police: Burned body found in NYC apartment
text:
NEW YORK (AP) - Police are investigating the death of a woman whose burned body was found in a New York City apartment.
Officers made the discovery at about 4 a.m. Saturday after responding to a 911 call reporting a possible assault in the Jamaica section of Queens. They found the woman alone in a third-floor apartment with burns on her body.
Authorities say 28-year-old Miriam Velez-Samayoa was pronounced dead at the scene. The medical examiner was to determine a cause of death.
Police say detectives are now trying to find her boyfriend, Carlos Leon, who they say is wanted for questioning.
Detectives say they are continuing to investigate. No arrests have been made.
